# Files in the repo root that must NOT be served as public Cloudflare assets.
# The assets directory is "." (see wrangler.jsonc), so without this every repo
# file - including .git - gets uploaded. Two reasons this matters:
#   1. Size: Workers rejects any single asset over 25 MiB; the .git pack is ~32 MiB,
#      which is exactly what failed the deploy.
#   2. Privacy: serving .git would expose the full source history publicly.
# Syntax is .gitignore-style.

.git/
.gitignore
.assetsignore

# Local AI / tooling config and notes
.claude/
research/
CLAUDE.md

# Dev-only scripts and deploy config (not needed at runtime)
*.bat
wrangler.jsonc

# Repo docs (not part of the app)
README.md
